<br>
Nutty huh?<br>
<br>
I dunno, we're talking about alliances here, and I am not really thinking on those lines, I am thinking more of the spur of the moment partnerings that may or may not occur, and then that's the end of it.<br>
<br>
One thing you said kind of hit a nerve though, I don't know if you meant it the way it sounded, but you made it seem like the people attending the raid for an allied or partnered effort, did not earn whatever they got out of it. I personally am of the opinion that if you helped kill the damn thing then you earned 100% of whatever you did or did not get out of it. I dunno maybe it's the early morning talking though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=revicus>Revicus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(2/22/03 11:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=534.topic&index=103>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re</span><hr size=1> I see the point made regarding rotation mobs. I agree these mobs should be done either on your own or if you choose the alliance route then you do all rotations as said Alliance.<br>
<br>
However the PoP Flag mobs I just don't see falling under the same rules as rotation mobs. I am of the state of mind that guilds should do it on their own to enjoy the sense of accomplishment however I don't look down upon other guilds helping eachother to flag people. <br>
<br>
People did it with pickup groups in trials to gain access to PoV/PoS. Lots of people even teamed up for BoT access and nobody said a word. However I can see why nobody complained since the zone size of PoV/PoS does accomodate a large number of people and the upper tier zones like CoD/HoH aren't as mega camp friendly.<br>
With the recent discussions here about teaming up it would appear that the complaints are mostly stemming from people who are trying to protect their content. <br>
The morals of some are being constantly thrown out as points of argument and reasoning why everyone should jump the bandwagon and frown upon these situations. Using power and threats, not direct threats, but implied threats such as perma camping flag mobs as a motivator to agree with the moral issues of teaming. <br>
That isn't right and certainly paints a jaded picture of our so called community that we pride ourselves in so much. <br>
Saying people didn't earn the flag if they teamed up to get it is assinine at best. If that is the case then there are alot of people in PoV/PoS/BoT that don't &quot;derserve to be there&quot; and I would be willing to bet some have moved on to more access of upper zones.<br>
I feel sorry for anyone who is not in a guild capable of taking down the flag mobs if the teaming is deemed to be &quot;unfair&quot; since they might as well quit playing if they want to see any of the upper end PoP content. <br>
Not to mention the non hardcore players who are good players but just don't have the time to become part of guild capable of taking down these mobs since they can't xp/aa for weeks on end to make the requirements to join a capable guild. <br>
Only option that makes sense is to either let people play the game and help eachother gain access to the new zones or put them all on rotation. But keep in mind putting the mobs on rotation slows EVERYONES progress. <br>
Progress is inevitable and by saying you can't team up to flag people only adds weight to the perception that the rulemakers are slowing down the rest to ensure their top dog spots and to control the release of content to people who are deemed unworthy according to the morals of the ones making the rules. <br>
And as far as the argument goes that flagging people will over crowd the zones... look at PoV/BoT ... NOT flagging people is overcrowding zones.. oh wait.. that's right... The rulemakers don't hunt there anymore so much do they? Ok makes sense now.. Nobody cares until it affects their stompin grounds. <br>
