<br>
Earth to Baysar, the RTA has had its rules and structures for how to kill big mobs since shortly after Hate/Fear came out, and it wasn’t based on my thoughts and feelings alone as you are accusing, it was the collective wishes of the server.  I don’t make those rules, but I am one of the entities (as are other GLs of other guilds on the Rathe) who help make them.  Just because I am the most prolific typist in this thread does not mean I alone have issue with the practice of teaming on mobs.  And yes, I do consider having morons in other zones with me as hurting my playtime and enjoyment, just as much as you do (remember it was your quote about BoT I referenced).  Having other people in zone who understand how to respect others’ camps and that dropping 14 Diaku Armsmen in someone else’s camp is a bad thing, I have no problems with.  People who have no clue about how to use invis properly in BoT, get a bad pull and dump 5 extra mobs on you as they hightail it to the zone, I do have a problem with.  As for me overstepping my bounds, when has expressing an opinion been “overstepping bounds”.  Not even close, all I have done is express my opinion, and engage in discussion with others who fail to see the historic precedents of the situation.  As for how much time would be wasted by permakilling said mobs, I think you grossly overestimate how much time it takes to kill Behemoth, he’s tough, but he’s not a long fight.  I also don’t agree with what that would do to other guilds taking legitimate shots at advancing, so my options are somewhat limited.  That leaves me with impressing on others the views myself and the majority of other major guilds have about why these kinds of actions are unfair to others, why they were unfair in the past, and why they are unfair now.<br>
